OL,7,FIn April 2022, the UK Home Affairs
OL,8,FCommittee published a report on
OL,9,Fspiking. The inquiry heard the results
OL,10,Ffrom a YouGov poll of 1,693 adults in
OL,11,Fwhich 11% of women and 6% of men
OL,12,Freported having been a victim of
OL,13,Fspiking.
OL,15,FIt also surveyed 1,895 victims, with
OL,16,F553 reporting mental health
OL,17,Fconsequences and 292 physical health
OL,18,Fconsequences of the event.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G17/18
