OL,5,Ctested
OL,7,FIn 2022, The Royal College of
OL,8,FEmergency Medicine (RCEM) issued a
OL,9,Fresponse to this report that
OL,10,Frecognised spiking "can cause serious
OL,11,Fdistress and harm to victims and cause
OL,12,Flasting damage to their mental, and in
OL,13,Fsome cases, physical health".
OL,15,FRCEM also acknowledged that "emergency
OL,16,Fdepartments are not able to provide
OL,17,Fforensic medical investigation and (it
OL,18,Fwelcomed) the committee's recognition
OL,19,Fthat alternative environments to allow
OL,20,Fproper investigation must be made
OL,21,Favailable".
